{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0214\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0214\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0214\"\nms.assetid: be1ef909-a53e-485f-a79b-b1cc56cead15\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0214\nPointers and fixed size buffers may only be used in an unsafe context  \n  \n Pointers can only be used with the [unsafe](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/unsafe.md) keyword. For more information, see [Unsafe Code and Pointers](../../csharp/programming-guide/unsafe-code-pointers/index.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates CS0214:  \n  \n```csharp  \n// CS0214.cs  \n// compile with: /target:library /unsafe  \npublic struct S  \n{  \n   public int a;  \n}  \n  \npublic class MyClass  \n{  \n   public static void Test()  \n   {  \n      S s = new S();  \n      S * s2 = &s;    // CS0214  \n      s2->a = 3;      // CS0214  \n      s.a = 0;  \n   }  \n  \n   // OK  \n   unsafe public static void Test2()  \n   {  \n      S s = new S();  \n      S * s2 = &s;  \n      s2->a = 3;  \n      s.a = 0;  \n   }  \n}  \n```\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,165],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0214\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0214\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0214\"\nms.assetid: be1ef909-a53e-485f-a79b-b1cc56cead15","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0214","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0214","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0214","pos":[0,21]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[172,193],"content":"Compiler Error CS0214","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0214","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0214","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"Pointers and fixed size buffers may only be used in an unsafe context","pos":[194,263]},{"content":"Pointers can only be used with the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>unsafe<ept id=\"p1\">](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/unsafe.md)</ept> keyword.","pos":[270,374],"source":"Pointers can only be used with the [unsafe](../../csharp/l